functionEntry.name: <globals/AnalogView/<>generateHandCoordinates>
functionEntry.documentation:
This function is used to generate the coordinates of the 4 corners of the polygon
used to draw a watch hand. The coordinates are generated with specified length,
tail length, and width and rotated around the center point at the provided angle.
0 degrees is at the 12 o'clock position, and increases in the clockwise direction.
centerPoint The center of the clock

angle Angle of the hand in radians

handLength The length of the hand from the center to point

tailLength The length of the tail of the hand

width The width of the watch hand

Returns The coordinates of the watch hand

functionEntry.name: onPowerBudgetExceeded
functionEntry.documentation:
The onPowerBudgetExceeded callback is called by the system if the
onPartialUpdate method exceeds the allowed power budget. If this occurs,
the system will stop invoking onPartialUpdate each second, so we notify the
view here to let the rendering methods know they should not be rendering a
second hand.
powerInfo Information about the power budget
